    "source_note": "E483 was removed from the EU approved list in April 2024 because the food industry failed to provide sufficient safety data for EFSA's re-evaluation. This doesn't necessarily mean E483 is unsafe, but rather that there wasn't enough modern scientific evidence to confirm its safety. The additive remains approved in the USA, Japan, Australia, and Canada."
